ThyssenKrupp’s Americas Chief Hans Fischer to Leave, FTD Says

-- B y   S t e f a n   N i c o l a
-- 
2011-12-02T07:14:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-02/thyssenkrupp-s-americas-chief-hans-fischer-to-leave-ftd-says.html
Hans Fischer, who heads German
steelmaker  ThyssenKrupp AG ’s Steel Americas business, is leaving
the company, the  Financial Times Deutschland  reported, citing
unidentified people close to the industry.  Fischer, who joined Essen-based ThyssenKrupp from
Salzgitter AG in February 2010, wants to take on a new task in
another company, the newspaper said, adding that he’s been
responsible for unprofitable plants in the U.S. and  Brazil .  Calls to ThyssenKrupp’s press office by Bloomberg News
weren’t immediately returned.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stefan Nicola in Berlin at 
 snicola2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Angela Cullen at   acullen8@bloomberg.net  